  "abstracts": [
    {
      "note": "description",
      "abstract": "Beginning with the 2030 model year, requires new passenger vehicles to be equipped with passive intelligent speed assistance systems.  Beginning 7/1/2030:  makes circumventing or tampering with an active intelligence speed assistance system a misdemeanor; requires the Department of Transportation to select a vendor for the installation and maintenance of active intelligent speed assistance systems; and allows the Judiciary to impose the installation of active intelligent speed assistance systems as an additional penalty and as part of a license suspension or revocation for repeat offenders of certain traffic violations."
    }
  ],
